-- MetLife Weighing Acquisitions in U.S. and Beyond, Kandarian Says
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-04-27T12:48:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/metlife-weighing-acquisitions-in-u-s-and-beyond-kandarian-says.html
MetLife Inc. (MET) , the largest U.S. life
insurer, said it is weighing acquisition opportunities in its
home country and beyond.  “We are still looking at properties not just in the United
States but globally that may make sense in terms of being a good
fit from our point of view strategically,” Chief Executive
Officer Steven Kandarian said today in a conference call.  To contact the reporter on this story:
